	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>afreeman</b><br /><i>I would just add that with the right AAs and focus items, mages can regen mana quite a bit better than this by 'canipet'ing', or chain-summoning and reclaiming their pets.  One post I saw suggested they could get over 40 regen a tick this way.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>True, but any mage will tell you in a hurry that pet canni is a downtime <i>only</i> tool.  The cast times on the pets that will actually give an appreciable amount of mana back (earth pets) have long cast times that are not conducive to quick mana regen in a 45 second fight.<br />
<br />
Back on topic though, just talk to your tank.  At least, thats what I do.  If I make the decision to dot, I let the tank know that I am going to e rooting the mob that Im dotting, so stay close to it.  90% of the time the tanks I group with have not minded and are actually appreciative of the 'help' in holding agro.  The only times that Ive had a problem with that tactic is when mobs might need reposistioning  mid fight because of add problems that the group doesnt want to mess with ( though I'm always ready to offtank any adds <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="wink" smilieid="5" />  )</p>
	
	
	
