	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>darkpaw</b><br /><i>but we lose that effecenicy if we have to tank from DoT agro when we could just convert those hp to mana anyways.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>OMG, someone else with a clue! Pull up a seat at the smart kid table... Welcome aboard pardner!<br />
<br />
Being hit is losing mana, on roughly a 2:1 scale. If a dot causes you to get a 600 pt love tap, that means it just cost an extra 300 mana. Roughly. I rarely get aggro with nukes and rains, deal better dps, and tend to have MORE mana lying around. Moreover, you sponge off the other healers. Draw aggro in elementals, and you will soak a fair amount more mana than your so called DoT efficiency saved. <br />
<br />
Who cares about crit dots? Until they make them worth casting, the aas are better spent improving our nukes more.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
