<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>stygiana</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2002<br />
	Location: Just below the deepest layer of the abyss
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>DoT agro is the result of a flaw in the code VI used when creating EQ. (well maybe it was done on purpose but i doubt that)<br />
<br />
What happens is that when you cast you DoT and it hits a mob you generate X agro. (if this DoT happens to have a DD part you actually Generate X agro from the DoT landing and Y Agro from the DD part hitting the mob)<br />
Each tick the DoT runs it will generate another X amount of Agro.<br />
<br />
As you all have noticed a Warrior is often not able to keep on him after a succesfull taunt when the tick hits.<br />
<br />
Welcome to a flaw in the system.<br />
<br />
The good news is that we make one hell of a tank in LDoN groups because 1 slow to pull and 1 poison dot and no Wizard will get the mobs attention.</p>
	
	
	
