	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Sciek Spellbottler</b><br /><i>DoTs are a nice BONUS you get as a shaman.  If you want better DoTs, play a necro.  If you the best nukes, play a wizard.  It's that simple.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>- Bonus? No, part of the class. <br />
<br />
Important facets of shaman class are:<br />
- DoTs<br />
- Heals<br />
- Buffs<br />
- Debuffs<br />
- Self mana regen.<br />
<br />
Now, a random class ... enchanter:<br />
- Mez.<br />
- Group mana regen.<br />
- Buffs.<br />
- Charm.<br />
- Debuffs.<br />
<br />
Another random class ... druid:<br />
- Snare<br />
- Ports, evacs<br />
- Nukes<br />
- Dots<br />
- Heals<br />
- Buffs<br />
<br />
Render near useless any core abilities and the class is hurting. Render nearly useless Mez and enchanters cry havoc. Render nearly useless druid nukes and they are up in arms. Why should shamans STF-U because one of their CORE abilities (DoTs) is broken?<br />
<br />
DoTs are one of the most efficient ways a shaman can deal damage. Saying it's just a "Bonus" is like saying that rogue backstab is just a bonus or mage/necro/bst pet is just a bonus.<br />
<br />
DoTs are broken. They need fixes.</p>
	
	
	
