	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Sciek Spellbottler</b><br /><i>Because a spell is high aggro it is broken?<br />
<br />
Slow and Tash are broken too?  How about Cripple?<br />
<br />
Some spells have high aggro associated with them.  Big deal.  If they were useless, I'd agree with you that they were broken.  But DoTs are far from useless, they are simply situational.  Situational is not the same as broken.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Not all spells that have high aggro are broken - just the ones that have unreasonably high aggro. Aggro should make sense.<br />
<br />
(I know there are tons of situations where aggro makes no sense at all - low-level stuns, ranger archery, etc... but one topic at a time.)<br />
<br />
If you're a mob fighting a bunch of PCs, and a wizard lands Strike of Solusek at the same time a shaman lands Blood of Saryrn, you'd go for the shaman. The wizard instantly did 2740 damage (at least) while the shaman is going to be doing a total of 2240 over the next 42 seconds. Yet the mob would go after the shaman? Why? It's like going after the guy who poisoned your tea with a slow-acting toxin while someone else is shooting at you with a high-powered rifle.<br />
<br />
DoTs are not an incidental part of our class, IMO. Up until Luclin and Funeral Pyre, we held the title for having the biggest DoTs in the game. Necros had the most variety, and could stack more for more damage... but Envenomed Bolt/Plague and Bane/Pox were king in their day. <br />
<br />
DoT spells have been overlooked for a long time. It's time for an improvement in efficiency and a reduction in aggro generation. People keep saying you can stack 200+ dps in DoTs, but how long does it take you to get all those spells up and running? There is a long ramping time before you get to max DPS with DoTs. Also, DoTs are limited by the number of debuff slots a mob has, while nukes have no such disadvantage.<br />
<br />
I don't think DoTs are useless, but I think they should be much more useful than they are in their current state.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220970" target="_blank">Sithrax</a><br />
iksar prophet - druzzil ro</div>
	
	
