	<p>While fighting Saryn today, we had a warrior with a bf and hate giver tanking.  I maloed, slowed, waited about a minute then started stacking blood, bane, scourge, pox, ultor.  About half way through the fight the tank died.  I thought I would be toast, but supprisingly the next warrior in line got aggro almost immediatly and the mob never gave me a second thought.  I didn't even need to wait after the new tank took over, i just continued my dot rotation.  Never once got aggro.  <br />
<br />
I think the biggest problem with our dots is the resist rates on raid mobs.  I don't have the LDON dots though, so I might not know what I'm talking about.<br />
<br />
I also think they could stand to tune the aggro on our posion line.  I handled it ok today, but thats not really typical.</p>
	
	
	
