	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>The only thing you said, that is right and NOT common knowledge is the fact that the aggro is independant from the counters.<br />
<br />
That doesn't mean everything you said was wrong, but most of the things that were right should at least be common knowledge. I'll try and point out the flaws as well as i can:<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />now this is an important one for us<br />
ur original position on the mobs hate list affects aggro <br />
if ur one of the first ones to aggro it ur gonna pop to the top of the hate list more easily<br />
since we must malos/slow mobs asap this affects us a lot<hr size="1" /></blockquote>This is incorrect. Unless you are fighting a mob with single Rampage. it doesn't matter at all when you get on the hate list. Of course casting early will sometimes get you killed, because the tank had less time to build aggro before your first cast.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />an important modifier is whether the spell was resisted or not<br />
in general if a spell is resisted it will generate more hate than if it actually lands<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Completely wrong. All spells have an innate amount of hate they generate and it's always the same whether it's resisted or not. <br />
Take the spell Concussion for instance. Concussion generates a very low amount of hate(i'd guestimate it's 1 point) and it lowers your current hate by 400. <br />
Every good wizard will tell you that no matter if Concussion is resisted or not, your hate will be lowered in the exact same was as if it had landed, which means that the innate hate(which in this case is -399) will always remain the same.<br />
<br />
The rest of what you said was actually informative and mostly right, but I'd hope everyone knows the mechanics by now.<br />
<br />
One important(the most important by far) aspect of hate generation in relation to mobs is another and hasn't been mentioned, but i won't spoil it now. Lucy and the like on top of all the spoilers given on various boards have gimped this game too much already.</p>
	
	
	
