	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>afreeman</b><br /><i><br />
<br />
-------------------------------------------------------------<br />
Originally Posted by Musicandor<br />
I think what Im trying to suggest is that the damage from any  kind of dot we use is not in proportion to the amount of aggro we generate, compared to other classes.<br />
-------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
I don't know if thats entirely true.  I group all the time with a 65/120+ necro, and he seems to pull aggro just as often as I do.  He usually opens with the group lifetap (I absolutely love that spell), then chains funeral pyre and maybe neurotoxin or another DoT, depending on mob health.  By the end of the battle, he has usually FD'ed at least once, sometimes twice, whereas I just have to root or endure the beating.<br />
<br />
Remember too that shammies usually slow first (big aggro), and possibly cripple (also big aggro) before we start with the DoTs.  Throw in a random heal here or there, and its gonna take a chain-casting hybrid or crazy-glue warrior to peel that mob off you.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>It is true that the necro DoT's generate similiar aggro, but they have FD to counteract that.  Shammys have practically no defense against aggro.  You arent going to root a boss mob, and he wouldnt summon you if you could FD.<br />
<br />
Other arguments imply that Shammys are not a damage dealing class, and therefore we shouldnt use DoT's, or if we do, very sparingly.  Well then what are Necros?  Main damage dealers like Wizards? No.  They are there for mostly support just like Shammys are.  So.....where is the Shammy version of FD?  Maybe one day we will see it.</p>
	
	
	
