	<!-- message -->
	<p>u just dont get it<br />
poison dots have high aggro<br />
thats just the way it is<br />
and this is not necessarily a bad thing ...<br />
<br />
90% of mob encounters in eq is about aggro management<br />
thats the main theme<br />
learn how to manage aggro<br />
<br />
if u WANT aggro then slow and stack poison dots on the mob then chain cripple<br />
bam noone can pry it off u with a crowbar :P<br />
<br />
if u DONT want aggro then u have to be more tactful and cast spells carefully<br />
just what u can cast and when depends on how well ur tank can hold aggro<br />
<br />
dis dots are low aggro<br />
curse dots are *low* aggro (be careful tho cuz they do a lot of dmg very quickly and will generate a lot of hate due to the dmg)<br />
our epic dot is low aggro<br />
our nukes and rains are low aggro<br />
all of those types of dmg appear to have no aggro modifiers on them so they just generate hate in proportion to the dmg they do<br />
<br />
learn how to manage aggro<br />
i dunno what else to tell u<br />
grouping/raiding in eq is all about managing aggro</p>
	
	
	
