grouping/raiding in eq is all about managing aggro</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I am well aware of what point I will aggro a mob with any spell I use.  I dont think any shammy got to lvl 65 without knowing where that fine line is.  That is not the point here however, this thread is not about aggro management.  This thread is about whether or not you think shammy DoT's, especially poison ones, cause too much aggro in relation to the spell damage from other classes.  Saying that "we are not a damage class" is meaningless.  Spells are made to be used.  Im not saying you can go hog-wild and DoT 20 stacked without expecting to die, but I dont think that stacking 3 DoTs is unreasonable.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Musicandor Freezeweaver<br />
65 Shaman<br />
Tindi Losi<br />
The Rathe</div>
	
	
