	<p>if u understand stacking 20 dots is unreasonable then whats so hard about understanding that poison dots are high aggro?<br />
<br />
a druid cannot stack fire dots either<br />
fire dots have mega aggro too<br />
stun has mega aggro<br />
a pally cannot chain stun a mob without drawing aggro<br />
are these spells *broken* too?<br />
<br />
bottom line dont use poison dots if u dont want aggro<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
viscerator <br />
poison dots had mega aggro before the patch that put counters on slow and tash<br />
now i cannot say if aggro from poison dots increased or not during this patch<br />
poison dots were already so much aggro that if i used them i was gonna get hit<br />
<br />
i used them often to move mobs during that period of my eq career<br />
it was easier to just toss a cpl dots on the mob and have it chase me to a corner then just tank it than it was to convince a clueless war that hes gonna get adds if he persists in fighting mobs right there :P<br />
<br />
so if there was an increase in hate from the counters - well it really didnt affect the spells anyway ...</p>
	
	
	
