	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Initially our poison dots did NOT have more aggro then our disease dots. <br />
<br />
This was recoded. Back in the day it was easier for pet or even a bard to keep aggro on a fully dotted mob. There is no way that happens now.<br />
<br />
It's pretty simple really; I don't think anyone would reasonably argue our disease dots are not fair aggro for the damage they do, nor the new curses even.<br />
<br />
Then why is it so completely out of whack what the Poison ones do? Because they do the same damage or less in half the time? Buzzz wrong...as pointed out several times, DD's do the same damage in 1/20 the time. Even the new curses are faster and don't draw the same aggro.</p>
	
	
	
