	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>So the question becomes: Why would I ever use disease dots if poison ones do the same damage in half the time?  This is probably what Sony was thinking when they made poison dots hella aggro, and disease dots...about half the aggro of their poison counterpart.  So how do they fix that?<br />
<br />
Lower even further the disease dot aggro to half of what it is currently.  Then, bring the poison dots to where the disease dots are now.  No one uses disease dots by themselves in a group, because the dot takes longer to finish then it takes to kill the mob, usually.  Possibly you'll use disease dots exclusively on a boss mob where they wont kill you with over aggro, and will usually run thier full course.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Musicandor Freezeweaver<br />
65 Shaman<br />
Tindi Losi<br />
The Rathe</div>
	
	
